1
00:00:10,320 --> 00:00:13,700
So… you’ve had a FWB before, right?

2
00:00:14,820 --> 00:00:16,840
Why do you want to know, Lal?

3
00:00:17,010 --> 00:00:19,040
Don’t tell me you have one.

4
00:00:20,520 --> 00:00:23,480
She works in Sales…
[JAN PLOYSHOMPOO AS LAL / JINGJING YU AS WINE]

5
00:00:23,480 --> 00:00:23,500
[JAN PLOYSHOMPOO AS LAL / JINGJING YU AS WINE]

6
00:00:23,500 --> 00:00:26,800
As you may know Sales
and Accounting don’t mix well.
[JAN PLOYSHOMPOO AS LAL / JINGJING YU AS WINE]

7
00:00:26,800 --> 00:00:27,130
[JAN PLOYSHOMPOO AS LAL / JINGJING YU AS WINE]

8
00:00:27,130 --> 00:00:28,450
At most offices, I mean.
[JAN PLOYSHOMPOO AS LAL / JINGJING YU AS WINE]

9
00:00:28,450 --> 00:00:28,470
[JAN PLOYSHOMPOO AS LAL / JINGJING YU AS WINE]

10
00:00:28,470 --> 00:00:30,000
That’s the case here as well.
[JAN PLOYSHOMPOO AS LAL / JINGJING YU AS WINE]

11
00:00:30,000 --> 00:00:30,010
[JAN PLOYSHOMPOO AS LAL / JINGJING YU AS WINE]

12
00:00:30,140 --> 00:00:33,780
Accounting always gets on our nerves,
whatever we do.

13
00:00:33,990 --> 00:00:37,050
I was told this is rather typical
for office workers.

14
00:00:37,270 --> 00:00:40,070
But one day, by total chance,

15
00:00:40,100 --> 00:00:44,680
they wake up next to each other in bed.

16
00:00:44,710 --> 00:00:45,760
Of course they’re surprised.

17
00:00:46,140 --> 00:00:47,900
Ah!!!!

18
00:00:48,940 --> 00:00:50,100
Are you okay, Lal?

19
00:00:50,590 --> 00:00:53,100
And I guess she must have liked it,

20
00:00:53,310 --> 00:00:56,470
since she asks me to be
her friend with benefits.

21
00:00:56,570 --> 00:00:59,630
But as friends with benefits,
we can’t let anyone at work find out.

22
00:00:59,650 --> 00:01:05,460
Because it’s the company’s policy
that colleagues don’t get involved sexually.

23
00:01:05,480 --> 00:01:06,070
Right.

24
00:01:06,100 --> 00:01:11,300
And thus begins the messy story
that is Enemies With Benefits.

25
00:01:11,470 --> 00:01:14,920
Lal, I want what happened last night to be
just a mistake between the two of us.

26
00:01:15,010 --> 00:01:16,320
No one can know about this.

27
00:01:16,400 --> 00:01:17,800
[COMES WITH NO LOSS]

28
00:01:17,820 --> 00:01:19,280
Do you want to be my FWB, Lal?

29
00:01:19,450 --> 00:01:19,890
Huh?

30
00:01:19,990 --> 00:01:23,200
Lal is actually friendly with everyone.

31
00:01:23,220 --> 00:01:27,250
She’s eager to be friends, connect,
and work with everyone.

32
00:01:27,280 --> 00:01:31,000
But there’s this one girl
who seems so uneager to work with me.

33
00:01:31,050 --> 00:01:33,050
She doesn’t accept her as a colleague at all.

34
00:01:33,070 --> 00:01:34,020
She always nitpicks.

35
00:01:34,040 --> 00:01:42,100
So reasonably Lal doesn’t want
to work with her, let alone be friends.

36
00:01:42,250 --> 00:01:45,820
From Wine’s perspective,
Wine’s worked at this company longer,

37
00:01:45,960 --> 00:01:47,370
while Lal is new.

38
00:01:47,400 --> 00:01:51,300
Everyone at work knows
what kind of person Wine is,

39
00:01:51,530 --> 00:01:53,300
and how she does her job.

40
00:01:53,540 --> 00:01:55,650
And so far, no one’s had any issues
with her, not until Lal.

41
00:01:55,670 --> 00:01:57,890
Lal is a straightforward person.

42
00:01:57,920 --> 00:02:02,240
What she thinks or feels,
even something negative, she lets it show.

43
00:02:02,270 --> 00:02:08,910
Wine has never met someone
who so openly shows their emotions.

44
00:02:08,940 --> 00:02:13,900
Even as friends with benefits,
Wine remains rather cold…

45
00:02:14,120 --> 00:02:15,220
At first.

46
00:02:15,960 --> 00:02:19,140
But she seems more… open later on.

47
00:02:20,060 --> 00:02:20,900
Right?

48
00:02:21,540 --> 00:02:23,780
Let’s say Wine keeps up a facade.

49
00:02:23,810 --> 00:02:25,020
A facade, huh?

50
00:02:25,160 --> 00:02:26,500
Wine loves her job.

51
00:02:26,520 --> 00:02:28,600
I’d say the same for Lal.

52
00:02:28,750 --> 00:02:31,670
So the two of us really don’t want
this secret to get out.

53
00:02:31,690 --> 00:02:33,810
And we put up such a good front about it.

54
00:02:33,980 --> 00:02:35,450
In front of people, we’re a certain way,

55
00:02:35,470 --> 00:02:37,200
but behind their backs,
we’re totally different.

56
00:02:37,600 --> 00:02:38,740
They’re doing a good job at it.
[KAPOOK PLOYNIRA AS TANGKWA]

57
00:02:38,740 --> 00:02:38,770
[KAPOOK PLOYNIRA AS TANGKWA]

58
00:02:38,770 --> 00:02:40,880
I totally can’t tell.
I honestly think they despise each other.
[KAPOOK PLOYNIRA AS TANGKWA]

59
00:02:40,880 --> 00:02:40,900
[KAPOOK PLOYNIRA AS TANGKWA]

60
00:02:40,900 --> 00:02:45,160
So how could two people who hate each other
be friends with benefits?
[KAPOOK PLOYNIRA AS TANGKWA]

61
00:02:45,420 --> 00:02:47,100
In this type of relationship,

62
00:02:47,380 --> 00:02:52,180
as friends with benefits,
don’t get your feelings involved.

63
00:02:52,220 --> 00:02:54,200
But as it goes on…

64
00:02:54,230 --> 00:02:56,090
It’s proximity, you know?

65
00:02:56,280 --> 00:02:59,700
Wine catches feelings,
but she doesn’t accept it.

66
00:02:59,910 --> 00:03:03,820
And so does Lal,
but she doesn’t let it show.

67
00:03:03,870 --> 00:03:05,110
It’s something like that.

68
00:03:05,140 --> 00:03:07,650
Because they’re restrained by this boundary
of being friends with benefits.

69
00:03:09,940 --> 00:03:12,050
Fine.

70
00:03:13,680 --> 00:03:15,700
I’ll try not to bite—

71
00:03:17,820 --> 00:03:20,100
I’ll try not to fight with you again.

72
00:03:23,110 --> 00:03:25,160
I’m Lallalin, Head of Sales.

73
00:03:25,280 --> 00:03:28,700
Our revenue growth this quarter
has met our target.

74
00:03:30,690 --> 00:03:32,910
I play Lal in this series.
[JAN PLOYSHOMPOO AS LAL]

75
00:03:32,910 --> 00:03:32,940
[JAN PLOYSHOMPOO AS LAL]

76
00:03:32,940 --> 00:03:34,120
Lallalin.
[JAN PLOYSHOMPOO AS LAL]

77
00:03:34,120 --> 00:03:34,150
[JAN PLOYSHOMPOO AS LAL]

78
00:03:34,150 --> 00:03:35,440
She’s the Head of Sales.
[JAN PLOYSHOMPOO AS LAL]

79
00:03:35,630 --> 00:03:39,130
Lal is a leader.

80
00:03:39,160 --> 00:03:41,670
She loves hyping people up.

81
00:03:41,700 --> 00:03:45,540
And since she’s a leader,
she takes care of people,

82
00:03:45,570 --> 00:03:48,120
and always tries to make
every situation better.

83
00:03:48,150 --> 00:03:52,300
She thinks her team is her responsibility.

84
00:03:52,410 --> 00:03:56,360
She’s an eldest daughter as well,

85
00:03:56,380 --> 00:04:02,100
so naturally she takes care of people
and tries to carry everything all alone.

86
00:04:08,020 --> 00:04:14,370
Lal starts working
for this company with ambition.

87
00:04:14,400 --> 00:04:17,600
And then she meets the Accounting Team.

88
00:04:17,800 --> 00:04:19,820
Imagine working hard,

89
00:04:19,840 --> 00:04:24,580
only for this one person
to always oppose you in everything.

90
00:04:24,600 --> 00:04:30,460
So Lal wonders why this person
would make her job so much harder.

91
00:04:30,670 --> 00:04:36,700
And then, by chance,
they become friends with benefits.

92
00:04:37,070 --> 00:04:40,500
Her usual workaholic self is compromised.

93
00:04:40,800 --> 00:04:43,600
Her mind is occupied
with something else, too.

94
00:04:43,700 --> 00:04:48,640
She begins to wonder what they are,

95
00:04:48,660 --> 00:04:51,400
but keep telling herself
she doesn’t like Wine.

96
00:04:51,420 --> 00:04:53,000
And that’s her issue.

97
00:04:53,080 --> 00:04:56,730
And since she doesn’t want
to have to fuss over her love life,

98
00:04:56,760 --> 00:05:01,680
she keeps denying her feelings,
telling herself she doesn’t like Wine.

99
00:05:01,850 --> 00:05:05,740
So whether or not
she likes or doesn’t like Wine,

100
00:05:05,760 --> 00:05:07,690
you need to stay tuned.

101
00:05:08,580 --> 00:05:10,720
Next time,
I’ll make sure Vetaka understands

102
00:05:10,750 --> 00:05:11,890
not to mess with my system!

103
00:05:11,920 --> 00:05:13,220
I’ve been curious for a long time

104
00:05:13,240 --> 00:05:16,220
about the new sales supervisor
I haven’t properly met yet—

105
00:05:16,240 --> 00:05:17,300
what kind of person you really are.

106
00:05:17,330 --> 00:05:18,320
This looks like it’s going to be tough.

107
00:05:18,510 --> 00:05:22,130
Lal and I are actually similar.

108
00:05:22,160 --> 00:05:26,180
The way we think is similar,
and we’re both eldest daughters.

109
00:05:26,210 --> 00:05:30,880
So I really understand this character
in many situations.

110
00:05:31,210 --> 00:05:35,330
Lal quite surprises Wine
in almost every way.
[JINGJING YU AS WINE]

111
00:05:35,330 --> 00:05:35,350
[JINGJING YU AS WINE]

112
00:05:35,350 --> 00:05:36,080
Because she’s the opposite
of Wine in every way.
[JINGJING YU AS WINE]

113
00:05:36,080 --> 00:05:37,380
Because she’s the opposite
of Wine in every way.

114
00:05:37,410 --> 00:05:39,040
Lal says what she thinks.

115
00:05:39,060 --> 00:05:43,470
She’s the kind of person who can turn
every bad situation into a fun time.

116
00:05:44,270 --> 00:05:46,100
Don’t make that face.

117
00:05:46,510 --> 00:05:49,300
You barely texted me back all day.

118
00:05:51,850 --> 00:05:53,400
I’ve been busy.

119
00:05:53,890 --> 00:05:57,200
But leaving my texts unread all day
is unacceptable!

120
00:05:57,690 --> 00:06:01,000
Can’t you at least send me
a sticker or something?

121
00:06:02,340 --> 00:06:04,600
The hardest part of this series
is the intimate scenes.

122
00:06:04,780 --> 00:06:06,410
Because there is just a lot of that.

123
00:06:06,430 --> 00:06:08,100
Like… Oh, wow.

124
00:06:11,880 --> 00:06:15,120
I mean… my friend was asking.

125
00:06:15,420 --> 00:06:18,500
Is it your friend… or you?

126
00:06:19,860 --> 00:06:23,900
Lal loves beer.

127
00:06:24,010 --> 00:06:25,930
Celebrating a win? Drink some beer.

128
00:06:25,950 --> 00:06:27,500
Getting sad? Drink some beer.

129
00:06:27,540 --> 00:06:30,010
Being happy? Drink some beer.

130
00:06:30,030 --> 00:06:32,800
You’ll hear her yell “Cheers!” often.

131
00:06:36,430 --> 00:06:38,900
I don’t like Wine!

132
00:06:39,820 --> 00:06:41,630
P’Jan is like a puppy.

133
00:06:41,660 --> 00:06:44,770
She’s fun and lively.

134
00:06:44,790 --> 00:06:48,080
Her smiles are always so bright.

135
00:06:48,130 --> 00:06:50,300
Lal and P’Jan are similar in that regard.

136
00:06:50,370 --> 00:06:54,810
We joke a lot that P’Jan is just
being herself in this series.

137
00:07:06,380 --> 00:07:12,100
Jan has this talent of effortlessly
making her acting feel good and natural.

138
00:07:12,160 --> 00:07:16,530
So often when I am on set
would I hear P’Tle complimenting Jan like,

139
00:07:16,560 --> 00:07:18,800
“Jan, that’s so good.” or “Jan, exactly.”

140
00:07:18,840 --> 00:07:19,730
or “Jan, you’re so on point.”

141
00:07:19,750 --> 00:07:21,280
He compliments her so often.

142
00:07:21,310 --> 00:07:27,890
She has this clumsiness and swag,
and she nails Lal’s character down.

143
00:07:28,310 --> 00:07:29,000
(Now.)

144
00:07:30,800 --> 00:07:32,330
(Oh, careful.)

145
00:07:32,750 --> 00:07:33,260
(Cut.)

146
00:07:33,380 --> 00:07:35,100
(That’s perfect. Let’s do it.)

147
00:07:37,290 --> 00:07:38,840
Hello, Lal.

148
00:07:39,330 --> 00:07:42,300
Hello, Wine Vetaka.

149
00:07:43,780 --> 00:07:45,300
I play Wine.

150
00:07:45,370 --> 00:07:47,260
She works in Accounting.

151
00:07:47,290 --> 00:07:50,390
She’s worked at this company
for a long time now.

152
00:07:50,410 --> 00:07:55,100
As expected of the head of Accounting,
Wine is strict and very organized.

153
00:07:55,300 --> 00:07:56,900
Everyone’s scared of her.

154
00:07:57,560 --> 00:07:59,130
I’m Wine Vetaka, Head of Accounting.

155
00:07:59,150 --> 00:08:00,730
On behalf of the accounting team,

156
00:08:00,750 --> 00:08:02,430
we’d like to point out that product value
has been steadily declining.

157
00:08:02,450 --> 00:08:03,340
We need to cut off certain products.

158
00:08:03,360 --> 00:08:04,180
And I’d like you to prepare a memo

159
00:08:04,200 --> 00:08:06,340
explaining why shipping costs
have increased from the previous cycle.

160
00:08:06,360 --> 00:08:09,540
With that many mistakes,
I suggest you take a new Excel course, Lal.

161
00:08:10,190 --> 00:08:12,940
It’s difficult because
she’s so different from who I am.

162
00:08:12,960 --> 00:08:16,780
Wine is super well-organized and strict.

163
00:08:16,810 --> 00:08:19,950
I’m usually fun and easy-going.

164
00:08:19,980 --> 00:08:22,270
But since I need to play her,
I have to stay in character.

165
00:08:22,300 --> 00:08:24,270
She’s like a straight line.

166
00:08:24,300 --> 00:08:26,610
She has no hobbies.
She has no social life.

167
00:08:26,640 --> 00:08:28,000
She goes straight home after work.

168
00:08:28,040 --> 00:08:32,100
What I value most is accuracy and rules.

169
00:08:32,160 --> 00:08:38,860
Wine is so detailed, by-the-book,
and allows not even a single mistake.

170
00:08:38,930 --> 00:08:40,960
Not even a tiny mistake. She’ll know.

171
00:08:40,980 --> 00:08:42,920
You can’t tell
if she’s a person or a robot.

172
00:08:42,940 --> 00:08:48,090
She does everything by the book
and doesn't let anything slide.

173
00:08:48,110 --> 00:08:49,230
She’s just neat like that.

174
00:08:49,580 --> 00:08:50,600
Done?

175
00:08:54,100 --> 00:08:56,100
It is done. Thank you.

176
00:08:56,550 --> 00:08:57,900
I mean, are you done?

177
00:08:58,050 --> 00:08:59,300
I need to use the copy machine.

178
00:09:00,060 --> 00:09:03,270
I admire her honesty.

179
00:09:03,290 --> 00:09:04,200
I think…

180
00:09:05,100 --> 00:09:06,820
I think Wine is such a good person.

181
00:09:07,130 --> 00:09:13,100
She’s a good person, and she fears people
would think badly of her,

182
00:09:13,530 --> 00:09:14,800
or don’t like her.

183
00:09:15,020 --> 00:09:20,020
So she removes herself from people
just to make it easy for everyone.

184
00:09:20,040 --> 00:09:23,390
She wants to make sure
she’s not hurting anyone.

185
00:09:23,420 --> 00:09:27,040
So she’ll choose to let herself get hurt
if it means other people don’t have to.

186
00:09:27,080 --> 00:09:29,800
“If it has to come to this,
I’ll take all the pain.”

187
00:09:29,830 --> 00:09:32,600
“I don’t want to cause you trouble,
and I don’t want you to know.”

188
00:09:32,690 --> 00:09:35,300
“So I’ll take it all.”
That’s the kind of person Wine is.

189
00:09:40,620 --> 00:09:44,880
P’Wine is one of the people
my character really loves.
[CIIZE RUTRICHA AS PROUD]

190
00:09:45,220 --> 00:09:50,700
She’s someone I want to save
from all the sadness and pain of the world.

191
00:09:50,770 --> 00:09:52,600
I just want her to be happy.

192
00:09:52,920 --> 00:09:55,820
Since Wine is such a closed-off woman,

193
00:09:55,910 --> 00:09:58,940
such an unsociable woman,

194
00:09:58,960 --> 00:10:02,000
she has her safe little box
where she absolutely refuses to leave.

195
00:10:02,420 --> 00:10:03,930
She can’t let anything happen to her.

196
00:10:03,950 --> 00:10:06,800
Everything has to be exactly
how she plans it in her little box.

197
00:10:06,820 --> 00:10:08,300
Because if anything deviates
from her plans,

198
00:10:08,570 --> 00:10:10,100
she will automatically feel like
she’s doing something wrong.

199
00:10:10,130 --> 00:10:12,770
But there’s a reason
why she is the way that she is.

200
00:10:12,800 --> 00:10:13,920
That raises the question:

201
00:10:13,950 --> 00:10:15,300
Why does it have to be Lal?

202
00:10:15,760 --> 00:10:19,160
What about Lal
makes Wine leap from her safe zone?

203
00:10:19,180 --> 00:10:24,500
Even with her closest circle,
like her secretary,

204
00:10:24,520 --> 00:10:26,800
she doesn’t open up like this.

205
00:10:26,940 --> 00:10:32,000
As the story progresses you will find out
why Wine chooses Lal.

206
00:10:32,160 --> 00:10:35,560
I just feel like I’ve met someone
who makes me feel warm inside.

207
00:10:35,660 --> 00:10:36,110
Huh?

208
00:10:36,140 --> 00:10:37,380
You’re actually going to have
a relationship?

209
00:10:38,300 --> 00:10:43,640
When Wine is drunk, she becomes
more honest about what she wants.

210
00:10:43,670 --> 00:10:47,580
She’s usually so well-contained
in her little box

211
00:10:47,610 --> 00:10:49,100
and fears venturing out of it.

212
00:10:49,210 --> 00:10:50,990
But when she’s drunk,

213
00:10:51,020 --> 00:10:56,200
she has this sudden courage
to get out there.

214
00:10:56,370 --> 00:10:58,470
You’re really drunk. I’ll call you a taxi.

215
00:10:58,690 --> 00:11:00,300
But I don’t want to go home.

216
00:11:01,850 --> 00:11:05,000
Well, she’s all strict and whatnot,
but when she’s drunk…

217
00:11:05,400 --> 00:11:07,500
The tigress becomes a kitten.

218
00:11:08,330 --> 00:11:10,000
How could that happen?

219
00:11:10,370 --> 00:11:12,880
She’s not all that confident in herself.

220
00:11:12,900 --> 00:11:15,330
Because she thinks
she hasn’t been acting for a long time.

221
00:11:15,450 --> 00:11:20,530
But I personally can vouch
that P’JingJing embodies Wine, like, 100%.

222
00:11:20,560 --> 00:11:25,300
When I’m in a scene with her, I totally
feel like I’m talking to my P’Wine.

223
00:11:26,980 --> 00:11:29,100
(Can you try that again?)

224
00:11:29,150 --> 00:11:30,100
This way?

225
00:11:30,130 --> 00:11:31,630
(On her shoulder.)

226
00:11:31,650 --> 00:11:32,500
Or this way?

227
00:11:32,530 --> 00:11:33,820
(Your right.)

228
00:11:35,090 --> 00:11:36,030
I read the novel.

229
00:11:36,050 --> 00:11:39,420
The novel describes her a certain way.

230
00:11:39,440 --> 00:11:43,830
And I was wondering how JingJing
would portray this character.

231
00:11:43,850 --> 00:11:46,780
I was curious how this would turn out.

232
00:11:46,810 --> 00:11:48,750
But in the workshop,

233
00:11:48,780 --> 00:11:53,020
and in the first quarter of filming,
in the first scene,

234
00:11:53,050 --> 00:11:56,470
she portrays Wine in such a sensual way.

235
00:11:56,500 --> 00:12:01,600
Even when she’s not moving,
she oozes this sensuality.

236
00:12:01,750 --> 00:12:04,520
She plays Wine in a version…

237
00:12:04,550 --> 00:12:06,300
that makes me understand
why Lal falls for her.

238
00:12:06,340 --> 00:12:09,090
JingJing is such a determined actor.

239
00:12:09,140 --> 00:12:11,490
And because she’s determined,
she does everything well.

240
00:12:11,520 --> 00:12:15,500
If you read her personal script,
you can see all the notes in the margins.

241
00:12:15,770 --> 00:12:17,940
I did a lot of preparing for this role.

242
00:12:17,980 --> 00:12:24,500
Because this is a main role,
I took more acting classes.

243
00:12:24,530 --> 00:12:28,150
I asked for more workshops,

244
00:12:28,190 --> 00:12:33,440
so I can be sure to bring Wine to life
in the most perfect way possible.

245
00:12:33,690 --> 00:12:34,910
I can feel her determination.

246
00:12:34,950 --> 00:12:36,690
I am a determined actor myself,

247
00:12:36,720 --> 00:12:39,500
so working with someone like this
makes it even more fun to go to work.

248
00:12:39,610 --> 00:12:40,770
Working is so fun.

249
00:12:40,790 --> 00:12:43,160
I'm not afraid of right or wrong
because there's no such thing.

250
00:12:43,180 --> 00:12:45,870
We’re just ready
to get through this together.

251
00:12:45,890 --> 00:12:47,900
So working has been really fun for me.

252
00:12:53,330 --> 00:12:54,180
That was hard!

253
00:13:16,620 --> 00:13:18,805
Actually, we’re not dating.

254
00:13:18,957 --> 00:13:21,240
I wouldn’t risk my career
for something like this.

255
00:13:21,340 --> 00:13:24,900
I love Jan and JingJing’s chemistry.

256
00:13:25,300 --> 00:13:27,740
I loved it right from the start
when I found out-

257
00:13:27,780 --> 00:13:30,100
this series was being made.
[KAPOOK PLOYNIRA AS TANGKWA]

258
00:13:30,220 --> 00:13:32,300
JanJingJing and KapookCiize.

259
00:13:32,340 --> 00:13:35,780
I called JingJing up right away,
“Did you see it, sis?”

260
00:13:36,060 --> 00:13:38,004
“I think this could work!”
“This could be a thing!”

261
00:13:38,032 --> 00:13:40,340
I tell her so often
that this could totally be a thing.

262
00:13:40,380 --> 00:13:45,580
They could be our first supermodel ship,
with legs for days.

263
00:13:45,620 --> 00:13:49,220
You know, the size difference ship?

264
00:13:49,260 --> 00:13:52,540
They’re the beyond 170cm ship.

265
00:13:52,660 --> 00:13:54,260
I make fun of them as the model ship.

266
00:13:54,420 --> 00:13:57,580
Their chemistry is off the chart
in the trailer.
[CIIZE RUTRICHA AS PROUD]

267
00:13:57,820 --> 00:14:00,580
I didn’t think
these two would make such a splash.

268
00:14:00,660 --> 00:14:05,380
But when I saw the trailer,
I was like, “Oh, wow! Yes!”

269
00:14:05,500 --> 00:14:11,780
P’Jan is naturally clumsy in real life,
while P’Jing is so caring.

270
00:14:12,140 --> 00:14:16,580
If someone doesn’t feel anything,
they wouldn’t overthink it like this.

271
00:14:18,860 --> 00:14:23,100
When I found out
I’d get to be in this series,
[JAN PLOYSHOMPOO AS LAL]

272
00:14:23,100 --> 00:14:23,820
[JAN PLOYSHOMPOO AS LAL]

273
00:14:23,820 --> 00:14:25,900
I went, “What? For real?”
[JAN PLOYSHOMPOO AS LAL]

274
00:14:25,900 --> 00:14:25,940
[JAN PLOYSHOMPOO AS LAL]

275
00:14:25,980 --> 00:14:29,260
I’ve been with GMMTV
for over 10 years now,

276
00:14:29,300 --> 00:14:33,980
and yes, I did get some sapphic roles,
but none of them have been main roles.

277
00:14:34,020 --> 00:14:36,700
But I remember the day
I got a call from someone,

278
00:14:36,740 --> 00:14:41,740
telling me there’s this project
that’s perfect for me.

279
00:14:41,780 --> 00:14:44,940
I went, “Really? Are you serious?

280
00:14:44,980 --> 00:14:47,180
Okay! I’ll do it!”

281
00:14:47,380 --> 00:14:51,300
I was happy. My first reaction was that
I was really happy to be in this project.

282
00:14:51,340 --> 00:14:57,700
When I found out, I went and bought
the novel so I could read it.

283
00:14:58,220 --> 00:14:59,380
And it happened to be really fun.

284
00:14:59,420 --> 00:15:03,540
I couldn’t help but think it was fate.

285
00:15:03,580 --> 00:15:07,500
Not to mention the fact that
this character is exactly like me!

286
00:15:07,780 --> 00:15:10,980
We both take our job very seriously.
[JINGJING YU AS WINE]

287
00:15:10,980 --> 00:15:11,300
[JINGJING YU AS WINE]

288
00:15:11,340 --> 00:15:14,140
I can always tell
when she’s under pressure.

289
00:15:14,180 --> 00:15:16,380
We talked about this so much.

290
00:15:16,420 --> 00:15:18,940
P’Jan always asked me
after we wrapped up each day

291
00:15:18,980 --> 00:15:21,620
how the filming went.

292
00:15:21,660 --> 00:15:24,860
And when she’s stressed, I can sense it.

293
00:15:24,900 --> 00:15:27,164
I asked her how she was feeling
about the day

294
00:15:27,189 --> 00:15:28,580
and if there were any issues.

295
00:15:28,740 --> 00:15:31,168
To be frank,
working on this series isn’t easy.

296
00:15:31,198 --> 00:15:32,300
There’s this…

297
00:15:32,780 --> 00:15:35,900
When two people want to make
the best of what they’re doing,

298
00:15:35,940 --> 00:15:39,340
and I’m not saying that
having tremendous ambition is a bad thing,

299
00:15:39,380 --> 00:15:41,540
but when we’re so full of ambition,

300
00:15:41,580 --> 00:15:43,740
it can easily become a kind of pressure
we put on ourselves.

301
00:15:43,780 --> 00:15:45,900
Because we really want to make this good.

302
00:15:45,940 --> 00:15:47,500
We put everything into it.

303
00:15:50,540 --> 00:15:55,780
I worked with JingJing before
in Mu-Te-Luv.

304
00:15:55,820 --> 00:15:59,500
And I thought it was interesting.

305
00:15:59,540 --> 00:16:01,100
It felt easy.

306
00:16:01,140 --> 00:16:04,085
We didn’t need
a lot of tuning into each other.

307
00:16:04,114 --> 00:16:06,740
We weren’t awkward at all.

308
00:16:06,820 --> 00:16:13,660
So I nominated JingJing’s name
to the team for the audition.

309
00:16:13,700 --> 00:16:16,900
Because I’ve worked with her before
and I feel like we could make this work.

310
00:16:16,940 --> 00:16:19,940
I was quite nervous waiting
for who got the role.

311
00:16:19,980 --> 00:16:23,380
P’Jan and I talked
when we worked together last time.

312
00:16:23,940 --> 00:16:27,660
I told her that
if I really got to be in a series,

313
00:16:27,700 --> 00:16:29,197
it was her I’d love to work with.

314
00:16:29,231 --> 00:16:31,900
And she told me the same thing.

315
00:16:31,940 --> 00:16:34,882
You know, it feels kinda like
a dream come true moment.

316
00:16:34,909 --> 00:16:37,100
I was so happy
when I found out I got the role.

317
00:16:37,260 --> 00:16:40,580
I’m so happy to be in this project
and to work with P’Jan.

318
00:16:40,740 --> 00:16:42,180
I’m really happy to work with her.

319
00:16:42,220 --> 00:16:49,580
Working on this is easy
because we can talk about anything.

320
00:16:55,060 --> 00:16:56,020
(Her hair has dried.)

321
00:16:56,060 --> 00:16:56,900
(No!)

322
00:17:00,180 --> 00:17:01,100
(Ahh!)

323
00:17:02,740 --> 00:17:04,180
Jan left a bite mark.

324
00:17:05,180 --> 00:17:07,060
Since I’m new to this,
[JAN PLOYSHOMPOO AS LAL / JINGJING YU AS WINE]

325
00:17:07,060 --> 00:17:07,100
[JAN PLOYSHOMPOO AS LAL / JINGJING YU AS WINE]

326
00:17:07,100 --> 00:17:08,660
I didn’t fully grasp the concept
of acting yet.
[JAN PLOYSHOMPOO AS LAL / JINGJING YU AS WINE]

327
00:17:08,660 --> 00:17:10,180
I didn’t fully grasp the concept
of acting yet.

328
00:17:10,200 --> 00:17:13,140
The emotions in each scene
could be hard to nail.

329
00:17:13,180 --> 00:17:15,700
You know we don’t always
film in chronological order?

330
00:17:15,740 --> 00:17:19,300
We could be filming for Episode 2,
then 8, then back to 3.

331
00:17:19,500 --> 00:17:21,220
It’s just a lot
and sometimes I get confused.

332
00:17:21,260 --> 00:17:25,940
But P’Jan always slaps me right back
into shape, into the right mood.

333
00:17:26,340 --> 00:17:28,380
-We’re like this behind the camera.
-Exactly.

334
00:17:28,540 --> 00:17:30,980
I didn’t get it at first.

335
00:17:31,220 --> 00:17:35,940
I just went zoom, zoom, zoom,
and ruined the character’s dynamic.

336
00:17:35,980 --> 00:17:38,300
So the scenes don’t feel very continued.

337
00:17:38,340 --> 00:17:41,844
She’d be like,
“Jing, I think it should be this or that.”

338
00:17:41,875 --> 00:17:43,420
And I got it.

339
00:17:43,540 --> 00:17:47,180
After that, I worked harder.

340
00:17:47,460 --> 00:17:49,300
The credits go to her determination,
really.

341
00:17:50,460 --> 00:17:54,380
She and I met for the first time
on the set of Hide & Sis.

342
00:17:54,420 --> 00:17:55,380
Yes.

343
00:17:56,100 --> 00:17:58,340
And P’Jan didn’t know at the time
my hearing’s bad.

344
00:17:58,380 --> 00:17:59,140
Or something.

345
00:17:59,180 --> 00:18:01,060
No, I knew.

346
00:18:01,100 --> 00:18:02,580
I just didn’t think it would be this bad.

347
00:18:02,620 --> 00:18:04,460
I’d be
“Jing, you’re stepping on my foot.”

348
00:18:04,500 --> 00:18:06,140
And she’d continue to do that.

349
00:18:06,420 --> 00:18:08,380
I have to go, “Jing! My foot!”

350
00:18:09,100 --> 00:18:10,780
She’d go, “Oh. I’m so sorry.”

351
00:18:11,900 --> 00:18:15,860
You’d think she’s a mean girl
from her resting face

352
00:18:15,900 --> 00:18:18,900
or from how fierce she looks.

353
00:18:18,940 --> 00:18:20,500
But actually she’s—

354
00:18:20,524 --> 00:18:22,100
Nice and gorgeous.

355
00:18:22,220 --> 00:18:23,460
-Wait for me to say it.
-Gorgeous and nice.

356
00:18:23,480 --> 00:18:24,980
-Wait for me.
-Okay.

357
00:18:25,900 --> 00:18:28,300
She’s a softie and nice.

358
00:18:28,325 --> 00:18:30,140
She’s so gentle.

359
00:18:30,180 --> 00:18:32,900
She’s not scary at all. Not even one bit.

360
00:18:32,940 --> 00:18:38,100
After meeting then,
I didn’t have the courage to be friends.

361
00:18:38,140 --> 00:18:39,900
I felt the same.

362
00:18:39,940 --> 00:18:42,380
I mean, we talked alright. But we didn’t…

363
00:18:42,500 --> 00:18:45,180
-We weren’t so playful.
-We didn’t go full ranting mode.

364
00:18:45,210 --> 00:18:48,125
Like I said, she looks kinda mean,

365
00:18:48,161 --> 00:18:50,740
-and I’m like older as well.
-She’s the big sister.

366
00:18:50,780 --> 00:18:54,460
So she didn’t think
she could be goofy with me.

367
00:18:54,700 --> 00:18:55,380
Ugh!

368
00:18:55,420 --> 00:18:57,380
What?! Oh, that was part of the script…

369
00:19:00,980 --> 00:19:01,860
I like you, Tangkwa.

370
00:19:01,940 --> 00:19:03,500
Wait—no!

371
00:19:03,780 --> 00:19:05,580
I need to think this through carefully.

372
00:19:07,340 --> 00:19:09,500
I play Tangkwa in the series.

373
00:19:09,540 --> 00:19:11,580
She works in Accounting.

374
00:19:11,700 --> 00:19:15,094
Tangkwa is calm and not very talkative.

375
00:19:15,127 --> 00:19:17,780
She keeps her feelings to herself.

376
00:19:17,900 --> 00:19:21,780
Her actions speak louder than her words
so she stays quiet.

377
00:19:22,100 --> 00:19:27,700
But when she lets loose,
she really goes all out.

378
00:19:27,740 --> 00:19:29,180
It’s like a different person entirely.

379
00:19:29,260 --> 00:19:31,380
But day-to-day, she’s well collected.

380
00:19:38,580 --> 00:19:44,060
Tangkwa is in Accounting,
and she’s always by P’Wine’s side.

381
00:19:44,100 --> 00:19:46,700
She’s basically her right-hand woman.

382
00:19:46,820 --> 00:19:51,755
Whatever it is, she’s there
to help Wine out with everything.

383
00:19:51,780 --> 00:19:54,100
When Wine needs help,
she turns to Tangkwa

384
00:19:54,140 --> 00:19:58,733
and she will get it done,
“I’ll look it up. Yes. Of course.”

385
00:19:58,768 --> 00:20:01,780
We come as a pair when it comes to work.

386
00:20:01,860 --> 00:20:05,500
Tangkwa is a little scared of Wine
and respects her.

387
00:20:05,540 --> 00:20:07,900
She works under me.

388
00:20:08,060 --> 00:20:09,900
I personally don’t think
Tangkwa is difficult to portray.

389
00:20:09,940 --> 00:20:12,740
For me, it’s not difficult portraying
a girl working in accounting.

390
00:20:12,780 --> 00:20:17,460
I take her as the calm and collected type.

391
00:20:17,620 --> 00:20:22,300
So I speak with a low voice
and stay still for her role.

392
00:20:22,380 --> 00:20:28,363
Tangkwa is friends with Numnim and Bas
who are in a different department,

393
00:20:28,390 --> 00:20:29,540
in Marketing.

394
00:20:29,660 --> 00:20:33,642
You have to know
that this company has a policy-

395
00:20:33,686 --> 00:20:35,380
that forbids colleagues to date.

396
00:20:35,580 --> 00:20:37,660
If they do, they have to keep it a secret.

397
00:20:37,700 --> 00:20:40,500
If it comes out, one of them
has to resign, or both have to.

398
00:20:40,540 --> 00:20:42,780
But since Tangkwa isn’t doing that,

399
00:20:42,820 --> 00:20:46,330
she’s friends with all the girls and boys.

400
00:20:46,362 --> 00:20:49,180
She doesn’t have to worry
about getting fired

401
00:20:49,220 --> 00:20:51,180
because she knows she’s not guilty.

402
00:20:51,780 --> 00:20:53,980
We in Accounting are suspecting something.

403
00:20:55,180 --> 00:20:56,780
I love Tangkwa’s wardrobe.

404
00:20:56,820 --> 00:20:59,700
I also love her personality,
and how she speaks.

405
00:20:59,740 --> 00:21:02,460
She doesn’t speak too fast or too slow,

406
00:21:02,500 --> 00:21:04,878
and she speaks clearly.

407
00:21:04,911 --> 00:21:07,340
She’s not high pitched like, “P’Wine!”

408
00:21:07,380 --> 00:21:10,980
She’s more like, “PWine. This is what I think.”
“Yes. Of course, P’Wine.”

409
00:21:11,020 --> 00:21:14,100
But you’ll see when Tangkwa lets loose.

410
00:21:14,140 --> 00:21:17,300
And I enjoy that when she lets loose,
she goes all out.

411
00:21:17,340 --> 00:21:24,580
She’s an office worker who,
when she lets loose, she doesn’t hold back.

412
00:21:26,980 --> 00:21:28,940
The first time I meet her,
I gauge her, like,

413
00:21:28,980 --> 00:21:32,540
“So this is the person
I have to work with?”

414
00:21:32,580 --> 00:21:35,860
“Oh, she looks like fun to tease.”

415
00:21:36,140 --> 00:21:37,580
We’ve worked together many times before.

416
00:21:37,620 --> 00:21:44,100
But this one, we’re more well behaved.

417
00:21:44,300 --> 00:21:48,940
From the first series to this one,
we’ve grown to be very close.

418
00:21:48,980 --> 00:21:51,300
So working together now just feels right.

419
00:21:51,331 --> 00:21:53,100
I’m really happy to work with her again.

420
00:21:57,180 --> 00:21:58,660
She’s a yapper.

421
00:21:58,740 --> 00:22:01,980
“I get to work with you.
I’m gonna call you P’Wine.”

422
00:22:02,020 --> 00:22:04,580
She’s very happy that her character
is younger than mine is.

423
00:22:04,780 --> 00:22:07,260
She’s the life of the party.

424
00:22:07,340 --> 00:22:08,980
She’s a funny girl.

425
00:22:16,500 --> 00:22:19,060
Kapook is a diva.

426
00:22:19,100 --> 00:22:22,540
She’s, like, always saying this and that.

427
00:22:22,580 --> 00:22:24,300
She’s a naturally funny person.

428
00:22:24,340 --> 00:22:27,540
Her comedic sense is real sharp.

429
00:22:27,620 --> 00:22:30,200
She has some
unexpected skits up her sleeve.

430
00:22:30,233 --> 00:22:34,220
And sometimes she doesn’t even
tell anyone until we’re filming.

431
00:22:34,260 --> 00:22:36,460
And it’s funny every time.

432
00:22:36,490 --> 00:22:37,340
She’s amazing.

433
00:22:37,380 --> 00:22:41,380
She’s our in-house yapper.

434
00:22:44,100 --> 00:22:44,940
Why are you zoning out?

435
00:22:47,060 --> 00:22:48,300
I want to be someone’s good love.

436
00:22:48,460 --> 00:22:51,460
Proud is quite feisty.

437
00:22:51,500 --> 00:22:53,180
She speaks her mind.

438
00:22:53,340 --> 00:22:54,900
She says what’s on her mind.

439
00:22:55,020 --> 00:22:57,900
She’s obvious in her likes and dislikes.

440
00:22:58,060 --> 00:22:59,380
She analyzes and suspects.

441
00:22:59,460 --> 00:23:02,980
Like, “What’s that? Wait. Hmm?”

442
00:23:03,100 --> 00:23:04,060
Something like that.

443
00:23:04,180 --> 00:23:07,660
Proud is a new employee,
but she’s talented.

444
00:23:07,700 --> 00:23:11,444
She’s talented, and she nitpicks people.

445
00:23:11,482 --> 00:23:14,100
“Is that even right? Is this correct?”

446
00:23:14,140 --> 00:23:15,540
This role isn’t really difficult.

447
00:23:15,580 --> 00:23:17,940
She’s not far off from who I am.

448
00:23:17,980 --> 00:23:21,100
I think I’m a bit feisty myself,

449
00:23:21,260 --> 00:23:24,500
so I slip into this character
quite easily.

450
00:23:24,620 --> 00:23:33,700
The hard part is the office lingo
that I’m not used to.

451
00:23:33,780 --> 00:23:35,340
I like Proud.

452
00:23:35,380 --> 00:23:36,780
I like that she’s straightforward.

453
00:23:36,900 --> 00:23:38,180
She acts the way she feels.

454
00:23:38,220 --> 00:23:39,740
And she’s such an open book.

455
00:23:39,780 --> 00:23:45,310
She knows her mind and she trusts herself.
That's what I like about her.

456
00:23:45,349 --> 00:23:47,300
I myself feel like
I’m always imposing on people.

457
00:23:47,338 --> 00:23:49,700
So I don’t always speak up
about what I want.

458
00:23:49,740 --> 00:23:51,700
I’m more like “Yes. Yes. Yes.”

459
00:23:51,740 --> 00:23:53,980
But Proud is like, “Hmm, hmm!”

460
00:23:54,020 --> 00:23:54,780
Like this.

461
00:23:54,980 --> 00:23:56,300
I love that about her.

462
00:24:03,860 --> 00:24:06,780
I think people are gonna suspect that…

463
00:24:06,807 --> 00:24:12,660
Proud is here to get between
the two of them, get them jealous.

464
00:24:12,824 --> 00:24:14,380
But there’s something more than just that.

465
00:24:14,620 --> 00:24:20,300
I think Proud is an important character
that will turn the story around.

466
00:24:20,340 --> 00:24:22,460
So I’d love it if you stay tuned.

467
00:24:23,380 --> 00:24:25,300
Hey, you wanna fight or what?

468
00:24:25,940 --> 00:24:26,900
Come at me!

469
00:24:27,540 --> 00:24:28,340
Proud, don’t.

470
00:24:35,380 --> 00:24:38,660
Proud talks like she has no filters.

471
00:24:38,700 --> 00:24:40,780
Sometimes what she says
doesn’t sound very nice.

472
00:24:40,820 --> 00:24:44,523
It makes you think
she’s a disrespectful newbie.

473
00:24:44,563 --> 00:24:46,060
So Tangkwa doesn’t like her

474
00:24:46,095 --> 00:24:52,140
and keeps an eye on her looking
for even a little mistake.

475
00:24:52,175 --> 00:24:54,140
Because she will surely get her for it.

476
00:24:54,180 --> 00:24:57,193
Everyone who doesn’t know Proud
doesn’t like her.

477
00:24:57,220 --> 00:24:58,980
But we’ve been friends since we were young

478
00:24:59,006 --> 00:25:01,500
so I know she doesn’t mean anything.

479
00:25:01,540 --> 00:25:03,700
She’s even trying to protect me.

480
00:25:03,820 --> 00:25:07,521
She’s a tiny thing yapping away at you,
like a force to be reckoned with.

481
00:25:07,566 --> 00:25:08,220
She’s adorable.

482
00:25:08,260 --> 00:25:09,980
She does such a good job portraying Proud.

483
00:25:10,020 --> 00:25:12,436
She always takes issues with me,

484
00:25:12,480 --> 00:25:16,042
suspecting there’s something going on
between Wine and me.

485
00:25:16,081 --> 00:25:18,300
She shots rapid fire words at me
and always argues with me.

486
00:25:18,460 --> 00:25:24,100
I think this character would be
really annoying if portrayed by an amateur.

487
00:25:24,128 --> 00:25:28,500
But Ciize manages to make Proud
so adorable.

488
00:25:28,540 --> 00:25:31,580
She’s like a kid
who always asks questions.

489
00:25:32,220 --> 00:25:33,540
“What? What?”

490
00:25:34,860 --> 00:25:37,380
(Can you step back a little?
It looks like you have a squint.)

491
00:25:38,940 --> 00:25:39,860
Where should she look?

492
00:25:39,891 --> 00:25:41,460
Let’s try again. Let’s try the other eye.

493
00:25:41,500 --> 00:25:42,820
(Try the left one.)

494
00:25:42,980 --> 00:25:43,820
It’s funny!

495
00:25:43,860 --> 00:25:47,180
I mean, it was funny
just reading the screenplay.

496
00:25:47,210 --> 00:25:50,920
In the screenplay, there are scenes
where they confront each other.

497
00:25:50,961 --> 00:25:55,500
Everyone was excited to see
Ciize and me go at it.

498
00:25:55,620 --> 00:25:59,620
It’s kinda similar
to our real life friendly banter.

499
00:25:59,660 --> 00:26:03,165
We always bicker.

500
00:26:03,213 --> 00:26:04,660
So it’s fun.

501
00:26:04,700 --> 00:26:06,500
We laughed so much while filming, though.

502
00:26:06,540 --> 00:26:11,613
I’d look at Ciize like this,
while she goes, “Yada-yada.”

503
00:26:11,640 --> 00:26:13,500
And I’d go “Yada-yada” back.

504
00:26:14,060 --> 00:26:16,297
It’s quite like real life.

505
00:26:16,501 --> 00:26:18,180
So it’s funny.

506
00:26:18,300 --> 00:26:19,620
How would you not know?

507
00:26:27,060 --> 00:26:29,860
I’d say it’s beyond my expectation.

508
00:26:29,900 --> 00:26:32,649
I did not think
there’d be more of KapookCiize.

509
00:26:32,691 --> 00:26:36,980
In the previous series,
we are heartbroken.

510
00:26:37,220 --> 00:26:39,780
We don’t end up together, you know?

511
00:26:39,980 --> 00:26:43,140
But people still want
to see us together in this one.

512
00:26:43,180 --> 00:26:46,180
They must have seen something in us.

513
00:26:46,340 --> 00:26:51,700
So I want to do my best to show
my gratitude for this second chance.

514
00:26:51,820 --> 00:26:56,243
I can’t say whether this will end well
but I’m thankful for the opportunity

515
00:26:56,270 --> 00:26:58,633
and I will try my best on my part.

516
00:26:58,660 --> 00:27:03,180
I just feel so at ease working with Ciize.

517
00:27:40,400 --> 00:27:42,501
Did you and Wine take it somewhere else?

518
00:27:42,820 --> 00:27:43,340
Huh?

519
00:27:43,500 --> 00:27:46,381
Numnim and Bas or Ployphach and JJ
are with Jan.

520
00:27:46,410 --> 00:27:48,140
They are in the sales department.

521
00:27:48,300 --> 00:27:52,940
I’ve worked with Ployphach before,
but it was a drama series.

522
00:27:53,100 --> 00:28:00,553
She was like
“I’m worried whether I can act well".

523
00:28:00,590 --> 00:28:02,980
"I’m not very good at comedy,”

524
00:28:03,020 --> 00:28:06,180
-but when the time came, she did it.
-She’s good at comedy.

525
00:28:06,220 --> 00:28:08,180
Yes, her timing is very good.

526
00:28:08,220 --> 00:28:12,940
With her dedication, she’s very talented.

527
00:28:12,980 --> 00:28:14,060
She did very well.

528
00:28:14,100 --> 00:28:15,220
As for JJ, nothing needs to be said.

529
00:28:15,260 --> 00:28:15,978
He’s funny.

530
00:28:15,996 --> 00:28:16,780
Hilarious.

531
00:28:16,806 --> 00:28:20,940
He walks in and says one line
and can steal the whole scene.

532
00:28:21,100 --> 00:28:23,300
He adds color to this series.

533
00:28:24,140 --> 00:28:25,465
-A lot.
-A lot.

534
00:28:25,500 --> 00:28:26,860
These two are incredible.

535
00:28:27,990 --> 00:28:29,654
Let’s leave tomorrow.

536
00:28:30,900 --> 00:28:32,580
It’s too late to leave the office.

537
00:28:32,780 --> 00:28:33,900
I mean the company.

538
00:28:43,965 --> 00:28:47,260
Jamie is in the procurement department.
Every time she enters a scene…

539
00:28:47,300 --> 00:28:48,860
she is so Jamie.

540
00:28:48,860 --> 00:28:51,140
She speaks just like Jamie does.

541
00:28:51,180 --> 00:28:51,580
Really.

542
00:28:51,620 --> 00:28:57,300
Yes, Jamie has a slight mixed accent
when she speaks.

543
00:28:57,420 --> 00:28:59,340
She did great.

544
00:28:59,380 --> 00:29:01,900
And Jamie has to play someone
who’s older than me.

545
00:29:01,940 --> 00:29:05,180
She did so well playing a kind boss.

546
00:29:10,980 --> 00:29:16,020
Wine is toxic, so annoying, so naggy.

547
00:29:16,060 --> 00:29:16,740
This is Wine.

548
00:29:21,180 --> 00:29:25,900
Pakphoom is an older friend of Lal.

549
00:29:25,940 --> 00:29:28,460
She always consults Pakphoom.

550
00:29:28,500 --> 00:29:30,180
He gives advice and keeps her in check.

551
00:29:30,221 --> 00:29:36,700
P’Pompam was given a level 10 role,
but he performs at 1,000 or 10,000.

552
00:29:36,860 --> 00:29:40,620
In a video call scene,
I was like “Oh, wow…”

553
00:29:40,660 --> 00:29:42,300
And we had to film separately.

554
00:29:42,340 --> 00:29:46,300
I wasn’t sure if we were acting
on the same level.

555
00:29:46,380 --> 00:29:48,180
He is one of the people
who made those scenes…

556
00:29:48,220 --> 00:29:49,192
More fun.

557
00:29:49,234 --> 00:29:51,700
Yes, more fun because of who he is.

558
00:29:52,060 --> 00:29:55,900
Think carefully. Think with your toe.

559
00:29:57,024 --> 00:29:58,158
This looks like it’s going to be tough.

560
00:29:58,220 --> 00:29:59,140
Of course it is.

561
00:29:59,580 --> 00:30:01,820
Lal, there’s a welcome party tonight

562
00:30:01,860 --> 00:30:04,340
for staff visiting
from the Japan headquarters.

563
00:30:05,180 --> 00:30:09,060
I heard someone on set say
this role suits P’Golf

564
00:30:09,460 --> 00:30:15,260
because it’s a boss role
and every line fits her.

565
00:30:15,300 --> 00:30:19,660
Because when she was at Grammy,
she managed many departments,

566
00:30:19,692 --> 00:30:21,010
She managed many people.

567
00:30:21,044 --> 00:30:25,260
So when she plays P’Jantra,
it fits perfectly.

568
00:30:25,940 --> 00:30:30,500
Everyone, we’ll divide into teams
to compete.

569
00:30:30,540 --> 00:30:34,500
The winning team
will get a special prize from HR.

570
00:30:36,940 --> 00:30:41,780
P’Leo played Khun New,
the head of the PR department.

571
00:30:42,060 --> 00:30:44,020
P’Jan has to argue with P’Leo a lot.

572
00:30:44,180 --> 00:30:46,700
There are many scenes
where they meet and argue.

573
00:30:46,940 --> 00:30:51,380
He likes to speak sarcastically to her.

574
00:30:51,580 --> 00:30:55,340
-He tends to judge others.
-That’s who he is.

575
00:30:55,380 --> 00:30:56,401
P’Leo’s script is very long.

576
00:30:56,431 --> 00:30:57,380
P’Leo said,…

577
00:30:57,860 --> 00:31:03,260
“Today I have 6 lines, today 2 pages,
today only I speak.”

578
00:31:03,420 --> 00:31:04,660
He likes to complain to me.

579
00:31:04,740 --> 00:31:05,780
I told him,…

580
00:31:05,820 --> 00:31:08,140
“Come on, if you have 6 lines,
I have 6 lines too-

581
00:31:08,180 --> 00:31:09,980
because we have to argue.”

582
00:31:11,100 --> 00:31:12,180
Come on, Miss Lal.

583
00:31:14,060 --> 00:31:17,180
We work together, we should be allies.

584
00:31:18,860 --> 00:31:20,220
Let’s not be enemies.

585
00:31:20,340 --> 00:31:24,900
N’Mim plays Cheese, Wine’s best friend.

586
00:31:24,940 --> 00:31:26,860
We had to think about
how to act like best friends,

587
00:31:26,900 --> 00:31:28,500
not a mother and daughter.

588
00:31:29,020 --> 00:31:30,660
-You know what I mean?
-Because she’s so tiny.

589
00:31:30,700 --> 00:31:35,002
She’s tiny and cute
while I look fierce and tall.

590
00:31:35,055 --> 00:31:37,020
I look intimidating.

591
00:31:37,050 --> 00:31:38,883
I was like “What should we do

592
00:31:38,913 --> 00:31:40,980
not to make us
look like a mom and a daughter?”

593
00:31:41,140 --> 00:31:43,020
Director P’Tle helped us.

594
00:31:43,060 --> 00:31:48,313
It took some time
until we could act like best friends.

595
00:31:48,350 --> 00:31:52,180
Once we clicked, filming became easier.

596
00:31:57,500 --> 00:32:00,100
Wow, he’s a very experienced actor.

597
00:32:00,180 --> 00:32:00,900
Yes.

598
00:32:01,100 --> 00:32:03,140
Jingjing has acted with P’Tae a lot.

599
00:32:03,180 --> 00:32:05,500
P’Tae is a character
who changes the story.

600
00:32:06,180 --> 00:32:13,050
P’Tae’s character twists the plot
and makes it more intense.

601
00:32:13,080 --> 00:32:13,483
Yes.

602
00:32:13,518 --> 00:32:15,060
It makes the story more interesting.

603
00:32:15,140 --> 00:32:20,980
P’Tae is very skilled
and a very nice senior.

604
00:32:21,060 --> 00:32:25,300
-Yes, we might see that he’s very muscular.
-Muscular.

605
00:32:25,340 --> 00:32:28,140
In scenes he might look intimidating,

606
00:32:28,180 --> 00:32:30,700
but in real life
he’s very nice and friendly.

607
00:32:30,740 --> 00:32:34,060
He always respects every actor.

608
00:32:34,100 --> 00:32:34,820
Yes.

609
00:32:34,852 --> 00:32:37,340
He’s very kind.
He always smiles when he speaks.

610
00:32:37,420 --> 00:32:40,300
The girls in the production
were crazy for him.

611
00:32:40,420 --> 00:32:42,300
-They were crazy for P’Tae.
-All of them.

612
00:32:43,660 --> 00:32:44,900
As for P’Mam…

613
00:32:45,180 --> 00:32:49,780
We’ve always seen P’Mam’s work.

614
00:32:50,180 --> 00:32:52,100
She plays a boss.

615
00:32:52,140 --> 00:32:54,420
She’s really intimidating.

616
00:32:54,450 --> 00:32:57,950
There’s one scene where I remember
how I felt acting with P’Mam.

617
00:32:57,989 --> 00:33:00,900
P’Mam called me in to talk about work.

618
00:33:01,140 --> 00:33:04,033
It was just a rehearsal,
but I sat like this,

619
00:33:04,061 --> 00:33:06,940
listening to her and got goosebumps.

620
00:33:07,020 --> 00:33:07,980
I was really scared.

621
00:33:08,020 --> 00:33:11,020
After the rehearsal,
an assistant came to ask me,

622
00:33:11,060 --> 00:33:12,500
“How was it? Did the room feel colder?”

623
00:33:12,540 --> 00:33:13,820
I said, “It did.”

624
00:33:14,500 --> 00:33:17,060
That was just a rehearsal, not actual filming.

625
00:33:17,100 --> 00:33:20,140
I was like “Oh wow, even in rehearsal
P’Mam is this serious.”

626
00:33:20,180 --> 00:33:23,380
During the actual shoot, I got goosebumps.

627
00:33:23,660 --> 00:33:25,780
But actually, P’Mam is nice as well.

628
00:33:25,820 --> 00:33:27,380
-So sweet.
-Very sweet.

629
00:33:27,420 --> 00:33:29,060
She talks to me, plays with me.

630
00:33:29,100 --> 00:33:32,330
-All the senior actors are very sweet.
-Everyone is lovely.

631
00:33:32,362 --> 00:33:36,300
-It’s a cheerful set.
-Yes, cheerful.

632
00:33:36,460 --> 00:33:40,820
Each actor in this series
fits their role so well.

633
00:33:40,849 --> 00:33:46,980
That makes working easier
because we don’t feel awkward.

634
00:33:47,020 --> 00:33:50,220
Everyone truly suits their role.

635
00:33:59,700 --> 00:34:00,780
I am that good.

636
00:34:10,980 --> 00:34:12,500
Just use your words, P’Tle.

637
00:34:50,280 --> 00:34:52,030
The atmosphere on this set is fun.

638
00:34:52,100 --> 00:34:53,460
There are many women…

639
00:34:53,620 --> 00:34:56,260
-It’s like going to an all-girls school.
-Yes, because it’s all women.

640
00:34:56,300 --> 00:34:57,700
There’s only one man in the story.

641
00:34:57,743 --> 00:34:59,500
That’s JJ.

642
00:34:59,700 --> 00:35:05,180
On set, when we all became close,
working became fun.

643
00:35:05,220 --> 00:35:07,065
It’s like meeting up…

644
00:35:07,123 --> 00:35:09,980
I don’t want to go into the scene.
I want to sit and chat with friends.

645
00:35:10,020 --> 00:35:11,300
-Yes.
-That’s it.

646
00:35:11,340 --> 00:35:16,033
-And eat.
-The food on set is delicious every day.

647
00:35:16,080 --> 00:35:18,180
There’s also food support from fans,

648
00:35:18,220 --> 00:35:21,180
both fans of P’Jan and P’Jingjing,

649
00:35:21,220 --> 00:35:24,060
and fans of Kapook and Ciize too.

650
00:35:24,100 --> 00:35:26,260
Sometimes there are food trucks
at the set.

651
00:35:26,297 --> 00:35:30,220
Sometimes it comes in big boxes
for us to choose from.

652
00:35:30,260 --> 00:35:32,380
That’s our motivation to work.

653
00:35:32,420 --> 00:35:33,140
Absolutely.

654
00:35:34,460 --> 00:35:37,900
For me, all the locations
in “Enemies With Benefits” are great.

655
00:35:37,940 --> 00:35:39,260
And most of them have A.C.

656
00:35:39,300 --> 00:35:42,587
-Because they’re office scenes.
-Exactly. I’m very happy.

657
00:35:42,652 --> 00:35:43,180
Fabulous.

658
00:35:43,220 --> 00:35:46,484
-Mostly office and condo scenes.
-Yes.

659
00:35:46,526 --> 00:35:48,500
Switching between the two.

660
00:35:49,100 --> 00:35:51,140
There’s also a trip to the sea.

661
00:35:52,140 --> 00:35:53,580
The hotel was good, very cute.

662
00:35:53,620 --> 00:35:54,780
We got to go on a trip, right?

663
00:35:54,815 --> 00:35:55,540
Yes.

664
00:35:55,580 --> 00:35:57,930
But the day we did activities
was quite hot.

665
00:35:57,975 --> 00:35:59,820
-Oh, the tree-planting activity.
-Tree planting.

666
00:35:59,860 --> 00:36:00,940
That was the only place that was hot.

667
00:36:00,980 --> 00:36:04,312
The tree-planting location
was quite exhausting and difficult.

668
00:36:04,354 --> 00:36:06,380
But aside from that,
everything was comfortable.

669
00:36:06,420 --> 00:36:08,940
Yes, but being with friends made it fun.

670
00:36:08,980 --> 00:36:09,660
Yes.

671
00:36:09,820 --> 00:36:11,700
“Step Nara” gang are all dancing.

672
00:36:13,740 --> 00:36:14,980
-See?
-What the heck?

673
00:36:24,460 --> 00:36:25,740
Come on, sales team!

674
00:36:26,020 --> 00:36:26,660
Go.

675
00:36:26,900 --> 00:36:27,500
Go.

676
00:36:27,900 --> 00:36:28,660
All Let’s go!

677
00:36:32,900 --> 00:36:35,494
This series has a lot of comedy scenes.
[JAN PLOYSHOMPOO AS LAL]

678
00:36:35,494 --> 00:36:35,540
[JAN PLOYSHOMPOO AS LAL]

679
00:36:35,540 --> 00:36:38,180
I mean, it has a lot of comedic timing.
[JAN PLOYSHOMPOO AS LAL]

680
00:36:38,180 --> 00:36:38,300
[JAN PLOYSHOMPOO AS LAL]

681
00:36:38,300 --> 00:36:41,060
I’ve acted in comedy before,
but it was a different style.
[JAN PLOYSHOMPOO AS LAL]

682
00:36:41,060 --> 00:36:41,940
I’ve acted in comedy before,
but it was a different style.

683
00:36:41,980 --> 00:36:46,843
But this one has fast timing
in P’Tle’s style.

684
00:36:46,880 --> 00:36:49,203
He clearly directed
that he wanted it this way,

685
00:36:49,236 --> 00:36:51,220
this kind of sharp acting.

686
00:36:51,260 --> 00:36:54,460
He added a lot of jokes,

687
00:36:54,500 --> 00:36:58,220
including sharper acting in each scene.

688
00:36:58,820 --> 00:36:59,860
Hey, P’Lal.

689
00:37:03,460 --> 00:37:04,260
How do I throw it?

690
00:37:04,420 --> 00:37:06,100
(Just throw it.)

691
00:37:07,540 --> 00:37:09,380
Throw it away. Do it.

692
00:37:09,500 --> 00:37:11,140
When I found out I’d be working
with P’Tle, I felt at ease.

693
00:37:11,180 --> 00:37:12,500
Yes, the Snap25 Production team.

694
00:37:12,540 --> 00:37:16,260
Actually, this team has worked with us
since “Pluto,”

695
00:37:16,660 --> 00:37:20,347
and they’re the team that built us too.

696
00:37:20,390 --> 00:37:23,460
That’s right, but this is the first project
P’Tle directed himself.

697
00:37:23,500 --> 00:37:26,500
Previously it was P’Katare.

698
00:37:26,860 --> 00:37:32,940
P’Tle is so sweet, easygoing,
and communicates well.

699
00:37:32,980 --> 00:37:36,180
He has a clear vision.

700
00:37:36,220 --> 00:37:40,420
If the work isn’t what he imagines,
he doesn’t waste time.

701
00:37:40,460 --> 00:37:46,580
He runs from the monitor to the set
and tells us, “Hey, I want it this way.”

702
00:37:46,620 --> 00:37:50,260
I feel that working with P’Tle
and the Snap25 team is very fast.

703
00:37:50,380 --> 00:37:55,940
Yes, we’ve worked with many directors,
but working with P’Tle feels faster.

704
00:37:55,980 --> 00:38:00,100
Maybe because
we’ve worked together before.

705
00:38:00,140 --> 00:38:04,780
Whatever he says, we understand
and can do what he wants.

706
00:38:04,860 --> 00:38:09,592
Yes, we and P’Tle see things the same way,
visualize the same things.

707
00:38:09,627 --> 00:38:14,140
And he uses clear words,
so it’s easy to understand.

708
00:38:14,180 --> 00:38:16,137
We don’t have to interpret what he says.

709
00:38:16,167 --> 00:38:16,540
True.

710
00:38:16,580 --> 00:38:18,220
Everything gets done very quickly.

711
00:38:18,260 --> 00:38:22,380
And we feel comfortable with the team,

712
00:38:22,420 --> 00:38:24,652
-whether it’s wardrobe, makeup, or hair.
-Yes.

713
00:38:24,689 --> 00:38:27,460
The cameramen
and all the crew understand us.

714
00:38:27,500 --> 00:38:29,180
Yes, they really take good care of us.

715
00:38:29,220 --> 00:38:31,380
Probably because
P’Tle used to be an actor.

716
00:38:31,420 --> 00:38:33,380
So he knows what actors need.

717
00:38:33,540 --> 00:38:35,180
That makes it easy to work.

718
00:38:35,220 --> 00:38:37,248
Sometimes we don’t even
have to say anything

719
00:38:37,275 --> 00:38:39,020
-because he tells us first.
-Yes.

720
00:38:39,620 --> 00:38:40,980
He’s already thought it through.

721
00:38:43,820 --> 00:38:44,460
(Cut!)

722
00:38:49,900 --> 00:38:50,940
Kiss her neck.

723
00:38:52,780 --> 00:38:56,060
Actually, my character
is feeling stressed.

724
00:38:56,100 --> 00:38:56,580
Really?

725
00:38:56,620 --> 00:38:58,820
Because Lal doesn’t want Wine to go.

726
00:38:58,860 --> 00:39:05,260
Wine comes in to talk about it,
but she doesn’t want to tease like that.

727
00:39:05,540 --> 00:39:07,180
For me, I think it can be played
in a cute way,

728
00:39:07,220 --> 00:39:10,820
like coming in to talk
in a friendly manner.

729
00:39:10,860 --> 00:39:12,460
Okay, I’ll go with that.

730
00:39:14,460 --> 00:39:18,660
When filming love scenes,
they told all the men to leave.

731
00:39:18,700 --> 00:39:22,020
The lighting team and others had to leave.

732
00:39:22,052 --> 00:39:29,780
The women from costume
and assistants took over instead.

733
00:39:29,820 --> 00:39:31,180
Everyone was female.

734
00:39:31,220 --> 00:39:34,060
And we didn’t use many people,
just about 3–4 people.

735
00:39:34,220 --> 00:39:38,780
The coordinator had to hold
the boom mic instead.

736
00:39:38,820 --> 00:39:40,390
Or hold the lights.

737
00:39:40,433 --> 00:39:42,820
The assistant director
had to hold the lights.

738
00:39:42,860 --> 00:39:48,543
The assistant director and P’Mednun from
the costume team acted as the cameraman.

739
00:39:48,580 --> 00:39:49,180
Yes.

740
00:39:49,220 --> 00:39:54,300
Because we had to change camera lenses,
and at that time our outfits weren’t safe.

741
00:39:54,340 --> 00:39:57,940
It was late,
so everyone there had to help each other.

742
00:39:58,140 --> 00:40:03,631
So we could film
without feeling shy or scared.

743
00:40:03,670 --> 00:40:04,420
It felt comfortable.

744
00:40:04,460 --> 00:40:06,380
So we could work to our fullest.

745
00:40:06,420 --> 00:40:07,380
Yes.

746
00:40:10,980 --> 00:40:12,580
Of course she was shy.

747
00:40:13,260 --> 00:40:14,460
Her ears went all red.

748
00:40:16,420 --> 00:40:17,180
Like…

749
00:40:17,580 --> 00:40:23,180
Even in the later shoots, I was still shy.

750
00:40:23,500 --> 00:40:27,740
The later shoots became more advanced.

751
00:40:28,380 --> 00:40:30,380
The scenes became more advanced.

752
00:40:30,460 --> 00:40:34,100
Later on, I wasn’t as shy anymore.

753
00:40:34,140 --> 00:40:35,940
When they told me to act
in an advanced way, I went all out.

754
00:40:35,980 --> 00:40:37,380
But P’Jan was like this.

755
00:40:38,700 --> 00:40:40,620
Her eyes looked distant.

756
00:40:40,660 --> 00:40:41,660
I would sit there zoning out.

757
00:40:41,700 --> 00:40:44,980
Before entering a scene,
I was like “Come on.”

758
00:40:46,980 --> 00:40:50,660
People who watched our EP.0 interview
might not understand

759
00:40:50,691 --> 00:40:52,780
why things happened like this.

760
00:40:52,940 --> 00:40:55,500
When you’ve watched EP.1, 2, 3, 4, 5
through 10,

761
00:40:55,540 --> 00:40:56,940
I want you to come back
and watch this clip again.

762
00:40:56,980 --> 00:40:59,660
You’ll understand why we’re like this.

763
00:40:59,700 --> 00:41:00,500
Like…

764
00:41:02,700 --> 00:41:03,743
Like this.

765
00:41:03,780 --> 00:41:06,180
Actually, it’s not just during acting.

766
00:41:06,220 --> 00:41:08,540
I can’t even watch myself act.

767
00:41:08,580 --> 00:41:11,180
We screamed like
“I can’t take this anymore.”

768
00:41:11,740 --> 00:41:12,540
So shy.

769
00:41:12,620 --> 00:41:14,980
I don’t even know
how I’m going to watch this series.

770
00:41:16,980 --> 00:41:17,940
It’s hard.

771
00:41:19,380 --> 00:41:21,043
You can look back at me sometimes.

772
00:41:21,100 --> 00:41:22,580
Yeah, you’ll get used to it.

773
00:41:24,660 --> 00:41:26,340
Wait, right here?

774
00:41:26,580 --> 00:41:28,300
All Ready!

775
00:41:29,540 --> 00:41:34,780
The soundtrack of this series
has slow songs,

776
00:41:34,820 --> 00:41:36,660
and of course fast songs too.

777
00:41:36,740 --> 00:41:40,580
And there’s another style of song
used in scenes like…

778
00:41:43,140 --> 00:41:45,380
I’m not gonna tell you. This song is like…

779
00:41:47,300 --> 00:41:48,660
Kind of like that.

780
00:41:49,460 --> 00:41:51,580
See? Her ears turn red when she’s shy.

781
00:41:53,300 --> 00:41:56,220
Every time we film a love scene.

782
00:41:57,620 --> 00:41:58,980
Not just singing.

783
00:42:00,980 --> 00:42:02,580
You’re always like this.

784
00:42:02,620 --> 00:42:04,580
That’s all we’re gonna say.

785
00:42:05,460 --> 00:42:07,100
-Yes, you’ll definitely hear it.
-You’ll definitely hear it.

786
00:42:07,140 --> 00:42:08,460
Not just singing.

787
00:42:11,380 --> 00:42:12,180
I’m Lal.

788
00:42:12,380 --> 00:42:13,180
I’m…

789
00:42:14,740 --> 00:42:15,980
Wine’s colleague.

790
00:42:17,860 --> 00:42:23,140
After watching the teaser,
I want to watch EP.1.

791
00:42:23,183 --> 00:42:25,060
I want to watch it all the way to the end.

792
00:42:25,140 --> 00:42:28,780
We acted in it, and we still
want to see how it turns out.

793
00:42:28,860 --> 00:42:30,100
-Goosebumps?
-I’m cold.

794
00:42:30,140 --> 00:42:30,860
Oh.

795
00:42:33,100 --> 00:42:37,660
I feel like each episode has its own hook.

796
00:42:37,700 --> 00:42:41,455
We want to present comedy.

797
00:42:41,500 --> 00:42:45,860
A romantic comedy
that’s cute and a little sexy.

798
00:42:45,980 --> 00:42:49,140
There are different storylines for you
to follow in each episode.

799
00:42:49,180 --> 00:42:54,024
From the middle episodes to the later ones,
it gets more intense.

800
00:42:54,067 --> 00:42:57,140
More intense with every episode.

801
00:42:57,300 --> 00:42:59,180
I want you all to support it.

802
00:42:59,340 --> 00:43:02,380
For those who don’t want to watch
something stressful,

803
00:43:02,580 --> 00:43:07,180
and want something light,
this series has a lot of comedy scenes.

804
00:43:07,380 --> 00:43:12,460
What surprised me is that I didn’t expect
this series to have drama.

805
00:43:12,500 --> 00:43:14,060
The drama in this series is also very heavy.

806
00:43:14,100 --> 00:43:14,780
Yes.

807
00:43:14,900 --> 00:43:18,500
What makes this series different
is that it’s light,

808
00:43:18,540 --> 00:43:21,980
but every episode has something
to keep you on edge.

809
00:43:22,140 --> 00:43:26,060
This episode might be like “Wow, so sexy.”

810
00:43:26,140 --> 00:43:29,100
The next might be “Hey, so funny.”

811
00:43:29,260 --> 00:43:32,260
Or “This episode is very dramatic.”

812
00:43:32,540 --> 00:43:35,260
You can’t separate them
because it has every flavor.

813
00:43:35,300 --> 00:43:36,224
It has many flavors.

814
00:43:36,252 --> 00:43:40,980
I think viewers will like this series
because it’s not stressful.

815
00:43:41,020 --> 00:43:42,820
It doesn’t make you think too much.

816
00:43:42,860 --> 00:43:43,500
Yes.

817
00:43:43,540 --> 00:43:46,500
You just feel along with the characters.

818
00:43:46,740 --> 00:43:51,260
Anyone who watches “Enemies With Benefits”
will fall in love with this series.

819
00:43:51,300 --> 00:43:53,580
You’ll definitely be waiting every week.

820
00:43:53,700 --> 00:43:56,643
Please follow the storylines
of P’Lal and Wine,

821
00:43:56,674 --> 00:43:59,540
and Tangkwa and Proud too.

822
00:43:59,860 --> 00:44:03,660
I want you to root for both couples.

823
00:44:03,700 --> 00:44:05,853
And please cheer for P’Kapook too,

824
00:44:05,891 --> 00:44:08,300
whether her character
will succeed in love this time.

825
00:44:11,820 --> 00:44:16,160
I like you in a way that’s more than
having to hide like this.

826
00:44:16,380 --> 00:44:17,460
If it’s too much,

827
00:44:17,660 --> 00:44:19,260
this relationship can end, Lal.

828
00:44:29,460 --> 00:44:33,780
Please support the character
Lallalin or Lal.

829
00:44:33,820 --> 00:44:40,792
This is a new role in my acting career,
and my first time playing GL.

830
00:44:40,828 --> 00:44:47,780
Please support and follow all the actors.

831
00:44:48,140 --> 00:44:50,060
I’m sure this series is fun

832
00:44:50,100 --> 00:44:53,580
and will definitely find a place
in everyone’s hearts.

833
00:44:53,620 --> 00:44:55,820
Please support the character, Wine.

834
00:44:55,860 --> 00:44:57,900
I put a lot of effort into this series.

835
00:44:58,140 --> 00:45:00,620
I want everyone to see our dedication.

836
00:45:00,660 --> 00:45:02,980
Please support Proud.
Please be kind to N’Proud.

837
00:45:03,020 --> 00:45:04,740
Don’t be annoy with her yet.

838
00:45:04,780 --> 00:45:06,270
Just wait for N’Proud.

839
00:45:06,307 --> 00:45:09,340
She’ll definitely come, just a bit later.

840
00:45:09,380 --> 00:45:12,300
Please cheer for N’Proud
and P’Tangkwa too.

841
00:45:12,380 --> 00:45:15,580
After being heartbroken in every series,

842
00:45:15,620 --> 00:45:18,140
if I succeed in love in this one,
I’ll treat everyone to hot pot.

843
00:45:18,180 --> 00:45:18,660
Kidding.

844
00:45:18,940 --> 00:45:21,601
Please support the series
“Enemies With Benefits.”

845
00:45:21,820 --> 00:45:24,980
Every Sunday at 830 pm on GMM25.

846
00:45:25,020 --> 00:45:28,180
Premiering May 3rd.

847
00:45:28,220 --> 00:45:29,460
Please support us.
